title.narrative: Reducing the burden of Tuberculosis in the Democratic Republic of Timor-Leste

description.narrative: Timor-Leste - Tuberculosis - Ministry of Health of the Democratic Republic of Timor-Leste - MOH. This program has the following goals: Decrease the prevalence of TB by 4 % by 2017 based on re-assessment of TB burden figures to be conducted in 2015 (this goal is derived from the NSP goal of 10% reduction by 2020). The objectives of this program are: Provide MDR diagnostic services for 75% of the estimated persons with suspected MDR TB by 2017; successfully treat at least 75 % of the diagnosed MDR patients (objective 3). Ensure successful treatment for 85 % of the enrolled patients (all forms) by 2017 (objective 2). Ensure availability of quality TB services, in line with current international standards and provided by qualified personnel at 70% of all facilities by 2017 (obejctive 5). Ensure timely and accurate recording and reporting from all (100%) of reporting centers by 2017 (objective 4). Detect at least 75% of incident TB cases( all forms) by 2017 (objective 1)
